==English==
===Etymology===
Named from [[w:Saint Matthew|St Matthew]], with reference to Matthew 25:29: ‘For unto every one that hath shall be given, and he shall have abundance: but from him that hath not shall be taken away even that which he hath.’ (KJV)

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'mæθju: ˌprɪnsɪpəl/}}

===Noun phrase===
'''[[Matthew]] [[principle]]'''
# the notion that more will be given to those that already have
#:*'''2002''': By including all citizens within the same insurance programs and by providing the economically active with clearly earnings-related benefits, the redistributive strategy of the encompassing model can be said to follow the '''Matthew principle''' of giving more to those who already have much. — ''Will Europe Work?'', ed. Martin Kohll & Mojca Novak (Routledge 2002, p.64)